CNCP v1 23515
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7276: Activated hook is not triggering when mounting childs of an async component",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:20.888368+00:00",
  "text": "Activated hook is not triggering when mounting childs of an async component\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.2.45\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- Enter the playground\r\n- Use the buttons to navigate between async components\n\n### What is expected?\n\nChild.vue being a child component of Parent.vue would trigger onActivated hook when mounted. following the docs: https://vuejs.org/guide/built-ins/keep-alive.html#lifecycle-of-cached-instance\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nChild component starts triggering onActivated after the initial mount\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "scope: keep-alive",
    "has PR"
  ],
